wiki.content: “Make Me Feel” is the lead single from Janelle Monáe’s third studio album Dirty Computer. The song was premiered by Zane Lowe on his Beats 1 radio show. Regarding the track, Monae told Lowe: "I actually had this title on this concept before my first album The ArchAndroid, and it scared me because a lot of the things that I knew that I needed to say were very deep, very personal, from the heart. You know, this is an extremely vulnerable album and it took me a while to make it because I’m a self editor." The song is vaguely reminiscent of “Kiss” by the late Prince who was both a friend to and a heavy influence on Janelle, appearing on her previous album The Electric Lady. Janelle also told The Guardian Prince was helping her with this album prior to his death. A music video for the song was released the same day as the single. The song was an instant critical darling, with Pitchfork naming it a “Best New Track” mere hours after its release. Read more on Last.fm.
